comments.body:
For elephant seals, you can see wrinkles on the snout.  Also, that bump on the nose which you can easily see on the light brown one's side-profile.  Also notice the nostrils:
https://ih1.redbubble.net/image.3443860.4397/flat,1000x1000,075,f.u1.jpg

************************************
For _Phoca_, notice the nostrils (like a 'v'):

http://marinebio.org/upload/_mammals/phoca-vitulina/5.jpg
@biohexx1 What's the easiest way to tell on the juveniles/females? The nose structure does look different now that you point it out
